Trust me if you were able to write the recurrence then the problem is just a cake for you. So now Try yourself and find the recurrence to solve this problem. If you were not able to figure out then no worries please read the full editorial. I will try to make it super easy for you. 
Lets dive deep what the problem is all about ? and note the imp points:
1. convert string S1 to string S2 
2. operation allowed are:
  a. insertion 
  b. deletion 
  c. replace 
3. return min number of operations 

Now lets observe the worst case : 
if s1 = "horse" and s2= "ros" then what my mind says is that delete every character of s1 and then insert every character of s2. so max number of operations are : N(length of s1) + M (length of s2). 
now optimized this; 
**One observation i can deduce is that if only insertion and deletion is allowed then this question will be similar to "min number of insertion/deletion to convert s1 to s2"** which is solved using the concept of lcs. 
but till now we have not consider the importance of replace operation. 

Now lets try to form the solution together. 

if you observe there can be only 2 cases formed (like every sting dp question)
**case 1:**
if s1[i]==s2[j] then no operation is require hence **F(i,j) = F(i-1,j-1)**
**case 2:**
if s1[i]!=s2[j] so there are 3 possibilites as given in question now if you were able to write the recurrence for each condition and take the min out of them . Hurrah!! you are done with the solution. Congrats!! . 
1. replace 
**F(i,j) = F(i-1,j-1)**
2. delete 
**F(i,j) = F(i-1,j)**
3. insert
**F(i,j)= F(i,j-1)**
ans = min (replace , delete, insert)

I hope you understand the approach. Lets see code of all approaches
**1. Memoization**
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minDistance(string word1, string word2) {
        int n= word1.size();
        int m= word2.size();
        vector<vector<int>> dp(n+1,vector<int>(m+1,-1));
        return solve(n-1,m-1,word1,word2,dp);
    }
    int solve(int i,int j,string word1,string word2,vector<vector<int>> &dp){

        if(i<0) return j+1;
        if(j<0) return i+1;
        if(dp[i][j]!=-1) return dp[i][j];

        if(word1[i]==word2[j]){
            return dp[i][j]=solve(i-1,j-1,word1,word2,dp);
        }

            char c= word1[i];
            word1[i]=word2[j];
            int rep= 1 + solve(i-1,j-1,word1,word2,dp);
            word1[i]=c;
            int del= 1+ solve(i-1,j,word1,word2,dp);
            int ins= 1+ solve(i,j-1,word1,word2,dp);
        return dp[i][j]=min(rep,min(del,ins));;
    }
};
```
**Time Complexity: O(n*m)
Space Complexity: O(stack space) + O(n*m)**

**2. Tabulation**
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minDistance(string word1, string word2) {
        int n= word1.size();
        int m= word2.size();
        int dp[n+1][m+1];
        for(int i=0;i<=m;i++){
            dp[0][i]= i;
        }
        for(int i=0;i<=n;i++){
            dp[i][0]=i;
        }
        for(int i=1;i<=n;i++){
            for(int j=1;j<=m;j++){
                if(word1[i-1]==word2[j-1]) dp[i][j]= dp[i-1][j-1];
                else {
                    dp[i][j]= 1 + min(dp[i-1][j-1],min(dp[i-1][j],dp[i][j-1]));
                }
            }
        }
        return dp[n][m];
```
**Time Complexity: O(n*m)
Space Complexity: O(n*m)
Runtime : 0ms (100% faster)**

