        //You found yourself how many factors 5 the number n! has: The number of factors 5 is n/5 + n/25 + n/125...  The number of factors 2 is n/2 + n/4 + n/8 ..., then number of factors 103 is n/103 + n/103^2 + n/103^3 ... and so on. (Applied to all prime dividers)
