        int[] pw = new int[len];
        pw[len-1]= a%mod;
        for(int i=len-2; i>=0; i--){
            pw[i] = pow(pw[i+1],10,mod);
        }
        int res = 1;
        for(int i=0; i<len; i++){
            int temp = pow(pw[i], b[i], mod);
            res = (temp * res)%mod;
        }
        return Long.valueOf(res).intValue();
    }
    public int pow(int x, int n, int mod){
        if(n==0)return 1;
        if(n == 1)return x%mod;
        int half = pow(x,n/2,mod);
        int extra = n%2==1?x:1;
        return (((half*half)%mod)*(extra%mod))%mod;
    }
```
**Approach 2: **
Checkout the "[Montgomery Modular Multiplication](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Montgomery_modular_multiplication)". It is also called Montgomery Powering Ladder.
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/5c6751b5-56da-4381-a695-f1004a49e34a_1635428856.58655.png)


The main approach in this method the conversion of `b` into binary string. My approach of conversion is definition not optimal.
```
class Solution {
    public int superPow(int a, int[] b) {
        int R0 = 1, R1 = a%1337, mod = 1337;
        LinkedList<Boolean> eBits = getBits(b);
        for(boolean bit: eBits){
            if(bit){
                R0 = (R0%mod * R1%mod) % mod;
                R1 = (R1%mod * R1%mod) % mod;
            }else{
                R1 = (R0%mod * R1%mod) % mod;
                R0 = (R0%mod * R0%mod) % mod;
            }
        }
        return R0;
    }
    private LinkedList<Boolean> getBits(int[] arr){
        Queue<Integer> rems = new LinkedList<>();
        LinkedList<Boolean> eBits = new LinkedList<>();
        int digit;
        for(int i=0; i<arr.length; i++){
            digit = arr[i];
            int adds = rems.size();
            while(digit > 0 || adds > 0){
                if(i == arr.length-1)
                    eBits.addFirst(digit%2 == 0?false:true);
                else
                    rems.offer(digit%2 == 0?0:5);
                digit /= 2;
                if(adds-- > 0)
                    digit += rems.poll();
            }
        }
        return eBits;
    }
}
```

