solutions.content:
Calculate the power first with iteration and mod by 1140(reason below).
φ( 1337 )
= φ( 7 x 191 ) where 7 and 191 are prime factor of 1337's factor decomposition
= φ( 7 ) x φ( 191 )
= ( 7 - 1 ) x ( 191 - 1 )
= 6 x 190
=1140
that means there are 1140 non negative numbers those are coprime to 1337.

calculate the pow till it is greater then 0.
if power is ODD then multiply with the temp number(for the first iteration temp is a).
if power is EVEN then multiply the temp number with itself and so that power will be half.

```
class Solution {
public:
    int superPow(int a, vector<int>& b) {

        long long temp = (long long)a;
        int num = 1, pow = 0, mod = 1337;

        for(auto x : b) pow = ((pow * 10) + x) % 1140;

        while(pow)
            if(pow & 1) {
                num = (num * temp) % mod;
                pow--;
            } else {
                temp = (temp * temp) % mod;
                pow >>= 1;
            }

        return num % mod;
	}
};
```

