**pow_mod** is quite similar to ordinary **pow** except computing remainder instead of product. Since **b** could be larger than 2^31 so **superPow** is added. Otherwise **pow_mod(a, c)** is enough with O(lgN), where N is the value of c.
Inside  **superPow**, I only call **pow_mod(a, 10)** with O(1). So the overall time complexity is O(N), where N is the length of b.
