**Idea :**
1. To understand the solution, knowledge of  [Fermat-Euler theorum](https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Euler%27s_theorem&oldid=1069867279) and how to calculate value of [Euler's totient function](https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Euler%27s_totient_function&oldid=1060227676) is required.

It is mentionable that [Fermat-Euler theorum](https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Euler%27s_theorem&oldid=1069867279) is a generalization of [Fermat's little theorem](https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Fermat%27s_little_theorem&oldid=1076742381). While fermat's little theorum is applicable only for prime numbers Fermat-Euler is applicable for all numbers.

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/fb41ba9f-f879-48d9-8517-a01b2c161b4f_1647211207.0776253.png)

2. Here [binary exponentiation](https://cp-algorithms.com/algebra/binary-exp.html) is used for fast exponentiation.

**Algorithm steps :**
1. Find power % 1140 from vector b;
2. FInd exponentiation by [binary exponentiation](https://cp-algorithms.com/algebra/binary-exp.html)

**code**
```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    int superPow(int a, vector<int>& b) {
		//calculation of power
        int pow = 0;
        for(auto x: b) pow = (10 * pow + x) % 1140;

		//exponentiation
        int ans = 1, t = a % 1337;

        while(pow){
            if(pow % 2)
                ans = t * ans % 1337;

            t = t * t % 1337;
            pow /= 2;
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
```

**Complexity Analysis**
Calculation to find power needs one iteration => O(N) 
Binary exponentiation takes O(logN) time on the exponent N.
As here power highest can be 1139 so, exponentiation part is roughly a contant

Total Complexity : O(N)

