[Wiki Modular_exponentiation](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modular_exponentiation)
using memory-efficent method to handle bit by bit
multiple the left right part  and mod by 1337 recursively

Example:

888<sup>666</sup> 
= (888<sup>66</sup>)<sup>10</sup> * 888<sup>6</sup> 
= ((888<sup>6</sup>)<sup>10</sup> * 888<sup>6</sup> )<sup>10</sup> * 888<sup>6</sup> 
= ((888<sup>6</sup> mod 1337)<sup>10</sup> mod 1337 * 888<sup>6</sup> mod 1337)<sup>10</sup> mod 1337 * 888<sup>6</sup> mod 1337
= ((1170)<sup>10</sup> mod 1337 * 1170)<sup>10</sup> mod 1337 * 1170
= (1198 * 1170 mod 1337)<sup>10</sup> mod 1337 * 1170
= 484<sup>10</sup> mod 1337 * 1170
= 918 * 1170 mod 1337
= 449

